metadata.name: Morixels Colab #2 MoriCar #58
metadata.description:
We all dream of having a car or we have

Some of us even talk to our car

And some of us see our car like a cartoon character.

This collection is not only an NFT but also a match
If you win one of the cups, in addition to a Super Rare edition, there are also prizes for the owners in the Primary market, which are as follows:
The lucky winners of the Gold Cup amount to 10 Tezos
The lucky winners of the Silver Cup amount to 5 Tezos
The lucky winners of the Bronze Cup amount to 3 Tezos

The MoriCar is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 7 (78 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 3,492,720 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of the most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website 👇

Website: https://morixels.com/

Twitter: @Morixels

by: @morteza_yousefy & @ardavan_
Made in 2022

metadata.name: SoulFish #78
metadata.description:
Named after the artist Wu Che-Yu, the soul fish was born in the void and crystallized from human emotions.

Fluttering silently and slowly, their bodies almost disappeared in the light of the deep sea.
The fish swims freely, and this is the happiness of the fish.
If we are not a fish, how do we know the joy of a fish?
How do we know that we do not know the joy of fish?
We will only learn about it when we come to the riverside.

Inspired by Zhuāngzǐ: "The Debate on the Joy of Fish" c. 3rd century BC

Interactivities:
> Key S: Save
> Holding mouse in different directions: Swim 
> Click and let the fish touch the Bubbles
> Key B: Toggle border
> Key P: Pause

metadata.name: Retrospect #28
metadata.description:
If it were possible, would you do things differently in retrospect?

A continuation of the exploration of the tension between freedom of choice and fate. Are the decisions we make imperfect, yet beautiful, or are they perfect, yet not beautiful?

meezwhite × July 19, 2022


To give the final result a slight retro feel, it is purposefully fuzzified and a filter layer of carefully picked 70s colors is mixed in. 

Click, tap or press [X] to invert colors.

License:
See LICENSE.md

This project uses p5.js.

metadata.name: Sound Therapy #38
metadata.description:
[ CLICK TO START THE SOUND ]

Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps rendering
Play the instrument by moving, clicking & dragging your cursor / finger

The combination of real-time graphics and generative music has always fascinated me, and what could be a better addition to the mix than a physics library for creating playful instruments. The instrument will play itself with a predefined pattern, but you can take over the controls and immerse yourself in the sound therapy. Enjoy and relax!

Keyboard
[ space ] - pause
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - pause

Created with Three.js + rapier.js

metadata.name: Crude Acceptance #99
metadata.description:
It was there when we arrived
    No owners, no gatekeepers
    The opportunity to explore
    The chance to transform
    What we are
    What we see
    And a trace will came with us
    And that way it will multiply
    As long as we allow
    To leave here a part of us
    It will be there when we leave
    No owners, no gatekeepers
    But itself



  Controls
  Format:
  'f' - switch square/full screen format

  View:

  'Arrow Up/Down' - Decrease/Increase distance to origin
  'Mouse Drag' - View Rotation


  Export:
  'x' - show/hide export menu
  'm' - quick canvas save


Created with p5.js (Javascript + GLSL) by Victor Doval @vicdoval (2022)
Designed to be seen in Google Chrome 102.0.5005.63
